Package graphpack.matching

graph path pattern matching facilities

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Matcher this is the principle class that is responsible for the pattern matching
Matcher.Cons used to pair two consecutive matchers together, this is vital for making sequences
Matcher.Edge matches a single edge
Matcher.FinishedWithNoResults empty (can be viewed as null) matcher, always returns no result
Matcher.FinishedWithSomeResults epsilon (can be viewed as an empty string "") matcher, may return some results (previously accumulated) but expects no further inputs
Matcher.Or matches two alternatives at the same time
Matcher.Repeat regular star operator
Predicate Represents a check which returns a boolean result
Predicate.And a predicate that is true IFF both inner predicates are true
Predicate.BinaryCombinator<T> a predicate that combines two inner predicates
Predicate.Comparison a predicate that compares two Number instances by using Double.compare(double, double)
Predicate.Comparison.GreaterOrEqualThan true IFF lhs >= rhs
Predicate.Comparison.GreaterThan true IFF lhs > rhs
Predicate.Comparison.LesserOrEqualThan true IFF lhs <= rhs
Predicate.Comparison.LesserThan true IFF lhs < rhs
Predicate.Equals a predicate that checks two values for equality
Number instances are checked using Double.compare(double, double)
other objects are checked using Object.equals(Object)
Predicate.Not a predicate that negates the value of an inner predicate
Predicate.Or a predicate that is true IFF at least one inner predicates are true
Result a single matched result
Result.SerializedUnassigned a serialized version of Result.Unassigned
Result.Unassigned an unassigned value (the value of a name that has not yet been matched)
ResultSet a multi-set of matched results (the same result can be repeated - in the future this behavior may be customized)
Value represents values in the specified expression
Value.Entity entity values are associated with an environment variable and they simply return the value from the environment
Value.Literal Literal values always return the same value (ignore the environment)
Value.Property Property values expect to find a certain entity in the environment which have a field of a certain property key.
